What is covered by my Select Plan for diabetic supplies and equipment? Outlines

You can get the following diabetic supplies at a pharmacy through home delivery, or at a retail network pharmacy. Your prescription copayments will apply.  Insulin products  Blood glucose strips  Blood and urine ketone/acetone test strips  Diabetic syringes, needles, and lancets  Continuous glucose monitoring systems (CGMs) 	 To get a CGM from your pharmacy, you must have a pre-authorization even if youve received 	  approval under your medical benefit 	 If you are overseas, you can get a CGM from a covered, retail pharmacy, if available, or 	  through mail order. 		 If you get a CGM from a local, non covered pharmacy, you must pay in full and file a claim 		   for reimbursement 		 If you are enrolled in the US Family Health Plan (USFHP), you must use a USFHP pharmacy 		  provider. Youre not eligible for the Select Plan Pharmacy Program. Outlines
